\title{Humanity in CS/PL, now more than ever}
\p{I really recommend [this article](https://koronkevi.ch/posts/humanity.html) by [[koronkebitch]]. It perfectly expresses some of the same thoughts that I've been having about CS, both research and teaching, in this AI-polluted age.}
\p{I am only in this business because of the people. My PhD advisor [Gabi](gckeller) and her husband [Manuel](chak), my mentor [Kai](kaie), my collaborators [Rob](rvg) and [Peter](hoefner) and [Christine](crizkallah) and [Zilin](zilinc), my colleagues [Ohad](ohad) and [James](jamesmckinna) and [Sam](slindley), and most of all my students over the years, among whom in particular I would name Andrew, Jiyeong, Tammy, Emmett, [Amy](sandwichman), [Ke](keshen) and [Rayhana](rayhana).}